.el .ds Aq '
.TH inspect 1  "inspect " 
.SH NAME
inspect \- Inspect contract information without executing
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBinspect\fR <\fB\-c\fR|\fB\-\-contract\fR> [\fB\-\-functions\fR] [\fB\-\-metadata\fR] [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-\-expected\-hash\fR] [\fB\-\-dependency\-graph\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Inspect contract information without executing
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-contract\fR \fI<CONTRACT>\fR
Path to the contract WASM file
.TP
\fB\-\-functions\fR
Show exported functions
.TP
\fB\-\-metadata\fR
Show contract metadata
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR
Output format: pretty (default) or json
.br

.br
[\fIpossible values: \fRpretty, json]
.TP
\fB\-\-expected\-hash\fR \fI<EXPECTED_HASH>\fR
Expected SHA\-256 hash of the WASM file. If provided, loading will fail if the computed hash does not match
.TP
\fB\-\-dependency\-graph\fR \fI<DEPENDENCY_GRAPH>\fR
Show cross\-contract dependency graph in specified format
.br

.br
[\fIpossible values: \fRdot, mermaid]
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH EXAMPLES
Display exported functions in pretty format (default):
.RS 4
\fBsoroban-debug inspect --contract mycontract.wasm --functions\fR
.RE
.PP
Export functions as JSON for machine-readable output:
.RS 4
\fBsoroban-debug inspect --contract mycontract.wasm --functions --format json\fR
.RE
.PP
Export all contract information including metadata as JSON:
.RS 4
\fBsoroban-debug inspect --contract mycontract.wasm --format json\fR
.RE
